    // If GCD is p, all elements in the subsequence must be multiples of p.
    // Let's consider only the elements nums[i] such that nums[i] % p === 0.
    // If we have at least two such elements, say a and b, and gcd(a, b) = p, we have a good subsequence.
    // If we have more than one such element, there's a possibility of a good subsequence.

    // A crucial observation: If there exists a subset of size >= 2 whose GCD is p, 
    // then there exists a pair whose GCD is p, OR the GCD of all elements in that subset is p.
    // The condition is: EXISTS non-empty subsequence S, |S| < n, such that GCD(S) = p.

    // Case 1: If there are at least two elements divisible by p, say x and y, and gcd(x, y) = p, we are done.
    // Case 2: If all elements divisible by p have GCD > p, or only one such element exists.

    // If there are at least two elements divisible by p, let them be {a_1, a_2, ..., a_k}, k >= 2.
    // If GCD({a_1, ..., a_k}) = p, then {a_1, ..., a_k} is a good subsequence if k < n. Since n >= 2, this is true if k <= n-1.
    // If GCD({a_1, ..., a_k}) = d > p, then any subsequence of this set will have GCD as a multiple of d, so it cannot be p.

    // The problem boils down to: Does there exist a subset S of size 2 <= |S| < n, such that GCD(S) = p?
    // If such a set exists, the condition is met.

    // Since we need to check existence after *every* update, we need an efficient check.
    // Let's count how many numbers are multiples of p.

    // Count of elements divisible by p
    let countP = 0;
    const isMultipleOfP = new Array(n).fill(false);
    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (nums[i] % p === 0) {
            isMultipleOfP[i] = true;
            countP++;
        }
    }

    // If countP < 2, it's impossible to form a subsequence of size >= 2, so no good subsequence exists.
    // If countP >= 2, we need to check if there is *any* pair (i, j), i != j, such that nums[i] % p == 0, nums[j] % p == 0, and gcd(nums[i], nums[j]) == p.
    // If we find such a pair, we have a good subsequence of size 2, and we are done.

    // If all pairs have GCD > p, we need to check larger subsets. However, if the GCD of a set S is p, then the GCD of any pair in S must be a multiple of p.
    // If we find *any* two numbers a, b such that gcd(a, b) = p, we are done. This is the strongest condition for size 2.

    // Let's stick to checking if *any* pair has GCD = p among the elements divisible by p.

    let existsGoodSubsequence = false;
    if (countP >= 2) {
        // Check all pairs of elements divisible by p
        for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (!isMultipleOfP[i]) continue;
            for (let j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if (!isMultipleOfP[j]) continue;
                if (gcd(nums[i], nums[j]) === p) {
                    existsGoodSubsequence = true;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (existsGoodSubsequence) break;
        }
    }

    let goodSubsequenceQueryCount = 0;

    for (let q = 0; q < queries.length; q++) {
        const [index, newValue] = queries[q];

        // Update the state (O(N) or better, but we are aiming for an efficient update)
