    // The strongest necessary condition we can easily check is the existence of a pair (i, j) such that gcd(nums[i], nums[j]) = p.
    // If this condition holds, |S|=2 < n (since n >= 2), and we have found a good subsequence.
    // Given the constraints, this pair-wise check is often the intended simplification for this type of problem.

